Japanese department store Mitsukoshi Corp. said  Thursday its pre-tax losses narrowed 6.4 percent to 5.4 billion yen (52  million dollars) in the year to March and forecast more red ink for the  current year.
The troubled affiliate of the Mitsui group of companies said global  revenues dropped 4.4 percent from a year earlier to 1,035 billion yen.
Mitsukoshi forecast another loss of 2.5 billion yen for the current year  with sales falling to 1,020 billion yen.
